/**
\page dev_doc-filtering The filtering mechanisms


The svutRunner class provide a simple way to filter which tests to execute of not. This is implemented on top of the abstract class svutTestFilter which provide a way to accept of reject some particular tests.


\section Thebasicfiltering The basic filtering


By default, we provide a simple implementation svutTestFilterBasic which work with a white list system :

 - if the list is empty, all the tests are accepted
 - if not, only the listed tests are accepted.

The rules can restrict the name by 3 ways :

<table>
<tr><td> <strong>Value</strong>  </td><td> <strong>Interpretation</strong> 
</td></tr><tr><td> <em>testCaseName::methodName</em> </td><td> Accept only a particular method of a particular test case. 
</td></tr><tr><td> <em>testCaseName::</em> </td><td> Accept all methods of a particular test case. 
</td></tr><tr><td> <em>::methodName</em> </td><td> Only check the method name independently of the test case name.
</td></tr></table>

